Euclidean metric, and  the 'unit metric' on -dimensional
hyperbolic space .  The corresponding symmetry groups are
 
For  we obviously require that .

We note that the ansatz (), for  and
, appears, after using an appropriate change of
coordinates, to be equivalent to that considered for supergravity
SD-branes in ref. . One can show that this is actually
not  the case. In order to bring solutions of the form
() with  to the form introduced
in ref.  we must find a change of coordinates such that
dt^2  = d^2  
