The roll of the tachyon 

We refer to a supergravity SD-brane as the field configuration
generated by a system composed of a large number, , of
microscopic SD-branes. As emphasized in section
, there is a single continuous
parameter that controls the dynamics of these fields, i.e. ,
. This is the parameter that
determines the relative importance of the unstable brane source.
Clearly, for  the open string tachyon
decouples from the bulk fields (no backreaction) and the
corresponding supergravity solutions will presumably be the
singular ones found in refs. .

In this section we present solutions with the symmetries of
SD-branes and a non-vanishing . We demonstrate that they
are generically non-singular.


Tachyon evolution in flat space 

The solutions relevant for SD-brane physics in Type II a,b
superstring theory could be the ones corresponding to an open
